Subject: [PATCH] Synchronization: annotate Linux futex mutex for TSan

The Linux Synchronization.Mutex implementation uses Swift Atomics and direct
futex syscalls rather than an intercepted pthread primitive. The installed
ThreadSanitizer runtime therefore cannot observe the mutex acquire/release
edges and reports every correctly protected inout access as a race.

Expose weak TSan hooks through _SynchronizationShims and invoke them after a
successful lock acquisition and before release. The weak symbols are absent in
normal processes; a predicted-cold symbol check preserves ordinary links and
the futex fast path without a runtime dependency. Instrumented clients now
receive the same happens-before relation that TSan derives automatically for
pthread_mutex_lock/unlock.

Sentinel: NUCLEUS_SWIFT_SOURCE_LINUX_MUTEX_TSAN

diff --git a/stdlib/public/SwiftShims/swift/shims/_SynchronizationShims.h b/stdlib/public/SwiftShims/swift/shims/_SynchronizationShims.h
index bb3477bca56..b08c113db30 100644
--- a/stdlib/public/SwiftShims/swift/shims/_SynchronizationShims.h
+++ b/stdlib/public/SwiftShims/swift/shims/_SynchronizationShims.h
@@ -24,0 +25,27 @@
+// NUCLEUS_SWIFT_SOURCE_LINUX_MUTEX_TSAN: The Linux Mutex is implemented
+// directly with atomics and futex syscalls, so
+// ThreadSanitizer cannot infer its acquire/release edges from an intercepted
+// pthread primitive. Weak runtime hooks and a predicted-cold symbol check keep
+// the ordinary path cheap while teaching instrumented clients about the
+// mutex's happens-before relation.
+#if defined(__cplusplus)
+extern "C" {
+#endif
+extern void __tsan_acquire(void *) __attribute__((weak));
+extern void __tsan_release(void *) __attribute__((weak));
+#if defined(__cplusplus)
+} // extern "C"
+#endif
+
+static inline void _swift_stdlib_tsan_acquire(void *addr) {
+  if (__builtin_expect(!!__tsan_acquire, 0)) {
+    __tsan_acquire(addr);
+  }
+}
+
+static inline void _swift_stdlib_tsan_release(void *addr) {
+  if (__builtin_expect(!!__tsan_release, 0)) {
+    __tsan_release(addr);
+  }
+}
+
diff --git a/stdlib/public/Synchronization/Mutex/LinuxImpl.swift b/stdlib/public/Synchronization/Mutex/LinuxImpl.swift
index 3f89b119923..a4a246f2f11 100644
--- a/stdlib/public/Synchronization/Mutex/LinuxImpl.swift
+++ b/stdlib/public/Synchronization/Mutex/LinuxImpl.swift
@@ -107,0 +108 @@ extension _MutexHandle {
+      unsafe _swift_stdlib_tsan_acquire(.init(storage._rawAddress))
@@ -111,0 +113 @@ extension _MutexHandle {
+    unsafe _swift_stdlib_tsan_acquire(.init(storage._rawAddress))
@@ -236 +238 @@ extension _MutexHandle {
-    return storage.compareExchange(
+    let acquired = storage.compareExchange(
@@ -241,0 +244,4 @@ extension _MutexHandle {
+    if acquired {
+      unsafe _swift_stdlib_tsan_acquire(.init(storage._rawAddress))
+    }
+    return acquired
@@ -247,0 +254 @@ extension _MutexHandle {
+    unsafe _swift_stdlib_tsan_release(.init(storage._rawAddress))
